üè¶ Bank Customer Churn Streamlit App

Executive AI Command Center for Predictive Customer Churn Analysis

This Streamlit app provides real-time insights into customer churn risk, enabling individual AI assessments, batch analysis, and what-if simulations to plan retention campaigns. The app is designed for business users, data analysts, and portfolio managers.

1Ô∏è‚É£ App Overview

Purpose:

Predict customer churn using a production-ready Random Forest model.

Provide a clear AI verdict per customer (Stay / Likely Stay / Likely Leave / Highly Leave).

Enable strategic decision-making via filters, ROI simulations, and risk dashboards.

Export individual or batch profiles for reporting or further analysis.

Who it‚Äôs for:

Bank executives, analysts, and retention teams.

Streamlined for non-technical users, with a guided UI.

Data Requirements:

Either use the built-in internal dataset (data/processed/Bank_Churn_Final_With_NumericClusters.csv) or upload a CSV with the required columns.

A template CSV is available in the sidebar.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Dashboard Modes

üè† Internal Database Mode

Uses the pre-loaded processed dataset.

Allows full filtering and reporting for the entire portfolio.

üì§ Client Upload Mode

Users can upload their own CSV.

Must include columns:

CustomerId, Surname, CreditScore, Geography, Gender, Age, Tenure, Balance, 
NumOfProducts, HasCrCard, IsActiveMember, EstimatedSalary


A template CSV is provided to guide formatting.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Filters & Global Portfolio Search

Geography: Multi-select by country.

Age Range: Slider for min/max age.

Balance Range: Slider for account balance in USD.

AI Risk Verdict: Multi-select to filter by predicted churn category.

Effect: All metrics, KPIs, and simulation results update automatically based on selected filters.

4Ô∏è‚É£ Top KPIs

Displayed at the top of the dashboard:

üí∞ Exposure: Total balance at risk for filtered portfolio.

üìâ Risk Avg: Average predicted churn probability.

üö® Critical Alerts: Number of high-risk customers (Prob ‚â• threshold).

ü§ñ AI Health: Simple progress bar indicating AI model readiness.

5Ô∏è‚É£ Single Customer AI Assessment

Predict churn for one customer at a time.

Inputs: Age, Tenure, Credit Score, Balance, Num of Products, Gender, Active Status, Credit Card, Estimated Salary.

Outputs:

AI Verdict (Stay / Likely Stay / Likely Leave / Highly Leave)

Churn Probability

Feature Table showing all columns including engineered features (ProductPerYear, balance_to_income, income_v_product)

Export: CSV of the individual profile.

Do‚Äôs & Don‚Äôts:

‚úÖ Ensure all fields are filled correctly.

‚úÖ Use realistic numeric ranges for reliable predictions.

‚ùå Avoid empty numeric fields.

‚ùå Non-standard column names in uploaded CSV can cause errors.

6Ô∏è‚É£ What-If Simulation & Retention ROI

Filter target segments by Age, Balance, and Campaign Cost.

Simulate retention campaigns with adjustable effectiveness.

Outputs:

Potential Capital Saved

Total Campaign Cost

ROI of targeted interventions

Graph: Risk Distribution of targeted customers.

Export: Financial simulation report as CSV.

7Ô∏è‚É£ AI Brain Health & Interpretability

Feature Impact Analysis: Bar chart of Random Forest feature importance.

